What is a computer network?
A computer network is a group of interconnected devices that share data and resources.
2. What is an IP address?
An IP address is a unique address assigned to a device to identify it on a network.
3. What is the difference between IPv4 and IPv6?
IPv4 is 32-bit (e.g., 192.168.1.1).
IPv6 is 128-bit (e.g., 2001:0db8::1). IPv6 supports more addresses.
4. What is DNS?
DNS (Domain Name System) converts domain names (google.com) into IP addresses.
5. What is DHCP?
DHCP automatically assigns IP addresses to devices in a network.
6. What is a subnet mask?
A subnet mask defines which part of an IP address is network and host.
7. What is a default gateway?
It is the router IP address used to communicate with other networks.
8. What is bandwidth?
Bandwidth is the amount of data that can be transmitted in a network per second.
